name: ExtensionExampleScenario_Process
title: Cross-version Extension `R5.ExampleScenario.process` for use in FHIR R4
description: This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element `ExampleScenario.process` for use in FHIR R4.
purpose:
This extension is part of the cross-version definitions generated to enable use of the
element `ExampleScenario.process` as defined in FHIR R5
in FHIR R4.

The source element is defined as:
`ExampleScenario.process` 0..* `BackboneElement`

Across FHIR versions, the element set has been mapped as:
*  R5: `ExampleScenario.process` 0..* `BackboneElement`
*  R4B: `ExampleScenario.process` 0..* `BackboneElement`
*  R4: `ExampleScenario.process` 0..* `BackboneElement`

Following are the generation technical comments:
Element `ExampleScenario.process` has is mapped to FHIR R4 element `ExampleScenario.process`, but has no comparisons.
Note available implied context: `ExampleScenario.process.step.process` because `ExampleScenario.process.step.process` is defined as a content reference to `ExampleScenario.process`.
